{ The line with c7-c5 and b7-b6 is the most common, by far, among King's Indian players when faced with the London System. In some books this is also called the Réti Reversed. }
8. O-O Bb7 9. Nbd2 Nc6 10. Bh2 cxd4 11. exd4 Bh6 12. Re1
{ is better and if Black follows the same plan with } 12... Nd5 13. Bf1 Bf4 14.
Bxf4 Nxf4 15. g3
{ White is left with the advantage; the f1-bishop will be redeployed on g2 and the absence of the black bishop from g7 can make itself felt }
