1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bf4 b6 4. e3
{ In a game by one of the co-authors, White was able to take advantage of the premature exchange on d4. After }
4... c5 5. Nbd2 cxd4 6. exd4 Bb7 7. Bd3 Be7 8. h3 O-O 9. a3 d6 10. O-O Nbd7 11.
c4 Re8 12. Re1
{ White had reached a theoretical position with an extra tempo, having played c2-c4 in one move, in De Prado-Sanchez, Spain tt 2011. }
