1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Qb6
{ One of Black's typical ideas is to move the queen to b6 to attack the weak point b2, but here this gives White the advantage, since he can just ignore the attack. In addition, capturing on b2 often allows White to repeat the position with a perpetual attack on the black queen, which will not suit Black if he is the stronger player. Instead }
5. Na3
{ is the best move, because it allows White to play Nc4 as well as Nb5. Let us consider some examples: }
5... cxd4 6. Nb5 Na6 7. exd4 d6 8. a4 Be7 9. Nd2
{ is better, with the idea of playing Nc4, e.g. } 9... d5 10. Bd3 Bd7 11. c3
O-O 12. O-O *

