{ In this section we have set you some exercises in strategy, based on the London System.  You are asked to find the best move or plan, appropriate to the position and in the spirit of this opening. Many of the examples are from games in the book.  You will need to remember some of the key points, which might be right in the opening or might be more of a middlegame character, but all of which you will need to know very well, in order to play the London System in the correct manner. }
1. -- *

