1... Bd6
{ Whether to play h2-h3 or not is one of the decisions that players of the London System get wrong most frequently. Against the Queens Indian, h2-h3 should be played only when Black has played ... Be7 and is threatening ...Nh5. If White plays h2-h3 prematurely, Black can equalise with the text move, since White has nothing better than to exchange on d6. White cannot play Bg3, since he would stand badly after ... Bxg3, when he has to recapture with the f-pawn. In contrast, with the pawn still on h2 White can recapture with the h-pawn, opening the h-file. }
2. Bxd6 cxd6 3. a4 Nc6 4. Nbd2 d5 5. Nb3 a5 { 0-1 in 40 moves. } *

