{ The following game went round the world and appeared in various magazines. Manuel held it in high regard above all because it was against the defence which he considered his nightmare: the Indian set-ups with the king's fianchetto. To my way of thinking, this present one is the best of Manuel Pereyra's games.  Manuel Pereyra Puebla-Oystein, Sande cr XI World Championship Final 1984. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. Bf4 Bg7 4. Nc3 d5 5. Qd2 O-O
{ After   5...Ne4  6.Nxe4  dxe4  7.Ne5  g5  8.Bxg5  f6  9.Bh6  Bxh6  10.Qxh6  fxe5  11.Qh5+  White has a big initiative according to Gennady Nesis. Now comes the familiar knight manoeuvre. }
6. Ne5 c5 7. dxc5 d4
{ Up to this moment I was firmly convinced that I was better, so much so that I believed I had a winning position. My opponent was certainly of a different opinion  (Sande, in Postsjakk, number 5, 1984)  . }
8. O-O-O Nh5 9. e3
{ An interesting sacrifice, says Nesis. If   9.Nf3  then  Nxf4  10.Qxf4  dxc3 !  11.Rxd8  cxb2+  12.Kb1  Rxd8  13.Ne5  Be6  14.Nd3  Rd4  15.e4  Bxa2+ ! }
9... g5
{ If it had been at all possible I would have preferred some other way to retain the advantage, but I couldn't see how, for example   9...Nxf4  10.exf4  Nc6  11.Nxc6  bxc6  12.Na4  +=  grants Black very slight compensation for the lost pawn  (Sande)  . }
10. Bxg5 Bxe5 11. g4
{ The first of many unexpected moves that struck me with blow after blow until the final knock-out  (Sande)  . }
11... Ng7
{ If   11...Bxg4  then  12.Rg1  Bxd1   12...Qd7  13.exd4  13.Bxe7+  Kh8  14.Bxd8 }
12. exd4 Bxg4
{ It looks dangerous to open the g-file but I didn't want to go down without a fight and I thought that this move gave me real chances of salvation  (Sande)  . If   12...Bf6  then  13.Bxf6  exf6  14.h3  (Nesis)  or   12...Bc7  13.Bh6  (Nesis) }
13. dxe5 Bxd1 14. Nd5 f6
{ This is the move I was relying on and I expected the reply 15. exf6 with a very unclear position, but  (Sande)  . Not   14...Bf3  15.Nxe7+  Kh8  16.Bd3 !  Bxh1  17.Bf6 }
15. Rg1
{ Here I was taken by surprise ! White is a rook down but doesn't flinch from sacrificing more pieces  (Sande)  . }
15... Bf3
{ If   15...fxg5  then  16.Qxg5  Rf7  17.e6  Qf8  18.exf7+  Qxf7  19.Bc4  or   15...Kh8  16.Bh6  Rg8  17.Qxd1 }
16. Bxf6 exf6
{ 16...Qxd5  17.Rxg7+  Kh8  18.Rg8+  Kxg8  19.Qg5+  Kf7  20.Qg7+  Ke6  21.Bh3+   16...Bxd5  17.Rxg7+  Kh8  18.Rxh7+  Kxh7  19.Bd3+  Kg8  20.Qg5+  Kf7  21.Qg6+  Ke6  22.Bf5# }
17. Qh6 Rf7 { Or   17...Qd7  18.e6 ! } 18. e6 Qxd5
{ If   18...Re7  then  19.Nxf6+  Kf8  20.Nxh7+  Kg8  21.Nf6+  Kf8  22.Qh8# }
19. exf7+ Kxf7 { Not   19...Qxf7  20.Bc4 ! } 20. Qxg7+ { After } 20... Ke8 21.
Qh8+ Kd7 22. Rg7+ Kc6 23. Qc8# *

