1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bf4 Nf6 4. e3 Be7 5. Nbd2 O-O 6. Bd3 b6 7. Ne5 Bb7 8. Qf3
Nbd7 9. h4 Nxe5 { If   9...c5  then  10.O-O-O  Rc8  11.g4  ↑ } 10. dxe5 Nd7 11.
O-O-O
{ Here the sacrifice should be examined; commentators have overlooked it, or were they keeping it to themselves ?   11.Bxh7+  Kxh7  12.Qh5+  Kg8  13.Nf3  f6  14.Ng5  fxg5  15.hxg5  Rf5  16.Qh7+  Kf7  17.g6+  Ke8  18.Qxg7  Bb4+  19.c3  Bf8  20.Qh8  Rg5  21.Qg8  Nxe5  22.Bxe5  Kd7  23.Rh7+  Be7  24.Qg7  Rxg2  25.Kf1  Rg5  26.f4  with very interesting play. }
11... Nc5 12. Bxh7+ Kxh7 13. Qh5+ Kg8 14. Nf3 f6
{ The move   14...g6 ?  is futile:  15.Qh6  Re8  16.Ng5 } 15. Ng5 fxg5 16. hxg5
Rf5
{ If   16...Bxg5  then  17.Bxg5  Qe8  18.Qh7+  Kf7  19.Rh6  is fatal for Black;  and   16...Rxf4  can be ruled out in view of  17.exf4  Qe8  18.Qh8+  Kf7  and now White mates with  19.g6+  Kxg6  20.Qh5# }
17. g4
{ Or   17.Qh7+  Kf7   17...Kf8  then  18.Qg6  wins.  18.g6+  Ke8  19.Qxg7  Kd7  and the king seems to escape. }
17... Rxg5 18. Bxg5 Bxg5 19. f4
{ The bishop will be captured and White will stand better.  If, e.g.,   19.Qh8+  Kf7  20.Qh5+  Kg8  21.Qh7+  Kf7  22.f4  Be7  23.Qh5+  g6  24.Qh7+  Ke8  25.Qxg6+  Kd7  26.Rh7   26.b4  Na4  27.Rh6  Qg8  26...Qe8  27.Rf7  Black seems to escape, but this needs further investigation. }
19... Bh6
{ 19...Be7  20.g5  and the attack cannot be parried  Of course,   19...Ne4 ?  loses to  20.fxg5  Nxg5  21.Rdf1 }
20. g5 Qe8 21. Qh4 Kh7 { 21...Kf7  then  22.gxh6  gxh6  23.Rdg1  ± } 22. Rdg1
Ne4
{ Not   22...d4 ?  because of  23.gxh6  Bxh1  24.hxg7+  Kg8  25.Qh8+  Kf7  26.g8=Q+  Qxg8  27.Qf6+  and wins. }
23. Rg4 d4 24. gxh6 g5
{ 24...g6  then  25.Rhg1  dxe3  26.Rxg6  Qxg6  27.Qe7+  Kxh6  28.Rh1+  Qh5  29.Qxe6+ }
25. fxg5 Qg6 26. exd4
{ Here   26.Rd1 !?  is interesting, e.g.  Rf8  27.Rxd4  Rf1+  28.Rd1  Rxd1+  29.Kxd1  ± }
26... Nf2 27. Rf1
{ Now   27.Qxf2  fails to  Bxh1  28.Qf6  Re8  but the simple   27.Rf4  Nxh1  28.Rf6  is good enough to win, e.g.  Qg8  29.g6+ }
27... Nxg4 28. Qxg4 Rg8 29. Rf6 Qxg5+ 30. Qxg5 Rxg5 31. Rxe6 Be4 32. Re7+ Kxh6
33. Rxc7
{ It is very difficult for White to win this; not only that, he has to exercise some care, in view of the weakness of his king, which is too exposed. }
33... a5 34. c4 Rg2 35. b3 Kg6
{ 35...Rxa2  36.d5  It was worth trying   35...Rc2+  36.Kd1  Rxa2  37.e6  Bc2+  38.Kc1  Bxb3  39.e7  Re2  40.d5  Kg6  41.d6  Kf7  42.Rc8  Ba4 }
36. e6 Kf6 37. d5 Rg8 38. Rb7 Ke5 39. Rxb6 Kd4 40. e7 Kc3
{ 40...Rg1+  41.Kb2  Rg2+  42.Ka3  Bb1  43.Ka4  Rxa2+  44.Kb5  Re2  45.d6  Bf5  46.c5 }
41. Kd1 Kd3 { 41...Bd3  42.Re6  Rg1+  43.Re1  Bc2+  44.Ke2 } 42. Ke1 Ke3 43.
Rf6 a4
{ 43...Bd3  44.Re6+  Be4  45.Rxe4+  Kxe4  46.d6  Ke3  47.Kf1  Kf3  48.d7  Rh8  49.Ke1  Ke3  50.e8=Q+ }
44. b4 a3 45. b5 Rc8 46. Ra6 Rh8 47. Rxa3+ Bd3 48. Rxd3+ Kxd3 49. Kf2 *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Pereyra Attack"]
[Black "Game 6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bf4 Nf6 4. e3 Be7 5. Nbd2 Nbd7 6. Bd3 O-O 7. Ne5 Re8
{ Maybe   7...Ne8 !?  Black does not seem to be aware of the threats he is facing. }
8. Qf3 Nf8 9. g4
{ With the threat of g4-g5: notice that the square f7 is insufficiently protected. }
9... Ng6
{ Black is accumulating pieces in the threatened sector, but it is in vain. }
10. g5 Nxe5
{ Forced.  If   10...Nd7  11.Nxf7 !  Kxf7  12.Bxc7+  winning the queen. } 11.
Bxe5 Nd7 12. Bxh7+ { An original variation on the theme. } 12... Kxh7 13. Qxf7
{ Isnt chess wonderful ! A position as if in suspense. White has sacrificed material and there are threats on all sides. A very strong attack is coming. }
13... Nxe5
{ This seems forced. .  If   13...Bf8  then  14.Qh5+  Kg8  15.g6 !  and wins. }
14. Qh5+ Kg8 15. dxe5 Bc5
{ 15...Bxg5  16.Rg1  Be7  17.Rxg7+ !  Kxg7  18.O-O-O  Rg8  19.Rg1+  Kf8  20.Qh6+  Kf7  21.Qh7+ }
16. g6 Qd7
{ With only a single attacking piece it would seem that White does not have much here, but that is what makes this game remarkable.  If   16...c6  then  17.Qh7+  Kf8  18.Qh8+  Ke7  19.Qxg7# }
17. Rg1 { Threatening Rg3-f3. } 17... Qb5
{ Giving the king more air.   17...Kf8  loses to  18.Qh8+  Ke7  19.Qh4+  Kf8  20.Rg3  Qb5  21.Rf3+  Kg8  22.Qh7# }
18. Rg3 Kf8
{ 18...Qxb2  19.Rf3 !  Qxa1+  20.Ke2  and the mate is unstoppable.. } 19. Qh4
{ Cutting off the retreat. } 19... Qd7 { Nothing can save Black now. } 20. Rf3+
