[Black "Game 7"]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 Nf6 2. d4 d5 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 c5 5. Nbd2 Nc6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Ne5
{ À la Pereyra. } 7... O-O 8. Bd3 Qc7 9. Ndf3 Ne4 { Black must occupy e4. } 10.
Bg3 g6
{ With this move Black forces White to do something about the threat of 11... Nxg3, followed by 11... Nxe5, winning a pawn.  If   10...Nxg3  then White plays  11.Bxh7+  Kxh7  12.hxg3+  Kg8  13.Ng5  g6  and now:  14.Ng4   14.Qg4 !?  f6  15.Nxe6  Nxe5  16.dxe5  Qg7  17.exd6  Kf7  18.Ng5+  Kg8  19.Ne6  14...f6  15.Qc2  f5   15...Ne7  16.Nh7  f5  17.Ngf6+  Kf7  18.Nxf8  Kxf6  19.Nh7+  Kg7  20.Ng5  ±  16.dxc5  fxg4   16...Bxc5 ?  17.Nh6+  Kg7  18.Nxf5+ !  17.cxd6  Qg7  18.f4  gxf3  19.gxf3  Rf5   19...e5  20.Qb3 !  20.f4  Rxg5  21.fxg5  Ne5  22.Rf1  Bd7  is unclear; }
11. Bxe4
{ White departs from the spirit of combinational play and attack on the black king, in order to reach an endgame with a knight against Black's bad queens bishop  (Needleman)  . }
11... dxe4 12. Nd2
{ Here   12.Ng5 !?  looks very interesting, e.g.  f5   12...Nxe5  13.Nxe4 !  +=  13.Nxc6   13.Nc4  is also playable, with advantage  13...Qxc6  14.Bxd6  Qxd6  15.h4  cxd4  16.Qxd4  Qxd4  17.cxd4  ∞ }
12... cxd4
{ If   12...Nxe5  then  13.dxe5  Bxe5  14.Nxe4  and the weak dark squares can be exploited by the knight. }
13. Nxc6
{ Trying to set problems.  Instead,   13.exd4 !?  Nxe5  14.dxe5  Bxe5  15.Nxe4  is similar to the previous note, but in this case everything depends on Black's advance  f5 }
13... dxe3 { 13...Qxc6  14.Bxd6  Qxd6  15.Nxe4  favours White. } 14. Nxe4 Bxg3
15. hxg3 Qxc6
{ Doing White a favour. In reality Black did not see his opponents twentieth move.  He needed to play   15...exf2+ !  16.Kxf2  Qxc6  17.Nf6+  Kg7  18.Nxh7  Qc5+  19.Qd4+  Qxd4+  20.cxd4  Rh8  21.Ng5  Bd7  22.Rxh8   22.Rac1  Rxh1  23.Rxh1  Rf8  24.g4  Bc6  =+  22...Rxh8  23.Rc1  Bc6  =+ }
16. Nf6+ Kg7 17. Qd4 e5 18. Qxe5 exf2+ 19. Kf1 Qa6+ 20. c4
{ Forcing Black to misplace his queen. The rest is simple. } 20... Qxc4+ 21.
Kxf2 Qc2+ 22. Kg1 Rh8 { And White forces mate. Black resigned } *

